<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851g.00/2–348: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Saigon</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-03T19:00:00-05:00">February 3, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>21. Mil Attaché Bangkok<note n="1" xml:id="d6fn1">Col. Reginald F. C.
                                    Vance.</note> reports Pham Ngoc Thach, one of Ho Chi Minh’s<note n="2" xml:id="d6fn2">President of the Provisional Government of
                                    Vietnam Democratic Republic.</note> chief lieutenants, in course
                                recent visit (1) said he departing for India 29 Jan with petition
                                signed by Ho Chi Minh requesting <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                                intervention (2) confirmed suspicion previously voiced by Amer
                                correspondent of imminent offensive which certain involve fighting
                                in city Saigon.</p>
                            <p>Sent Saigon as 21; rptd New Delhi as 79. Saigon repeat Hanoi.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>